{"name":"Citysoundmap","tagline":"Sound data logger using the Raspberry Pi and a digital sound meter","body":"City Sound Map\r\n\r\nSound Data Logger using the Raspberry Pi, digital sound sensor and Camera Module \r\n\r\n### Parts\r\n\r\n* [Digital sound meter](http://www.amazon.com/Professional-Digital-Pressure-Measurement-Detectors/dp/B00LL3Y074) - (Tonda SL-814)\r\n* [Raspberry Pi](http://www.adafruit.com/products/1914)\r\n* [Pi Camera Module](http://www.adafruit.com/products/1367)\r\n\r\n### Software/Scripts\r\n\r\n* Python script to record sound levels and image or video clips\r\n* Apache\r\n* d3.js\r\n\r\n***\r\n\r\nThis project uses a modified Tonda SL-814 digital sound meter weighted for pressure level A. The modifcations allow the meter to be powered from raspberry pi and remain in an always on state for continual polling.  \r\n\r\nI purchased [this model](http://www.amazon.com/NEEWER%C2%AE-Digital-Sound-Level-Meter/dp/B005JX2EZ2) \r\n\r\nThough, I recommend [this one](http://www.amazon.com/Professional-Digital-Pressure-Measurement-Detectors/dp/B00LL3Y074) as it comes with the special cable(non-standard USB), otherwise you'll have to modify a micro-usb cable.\r\n\r\nThe serial protocol has been reverse engineered and is available here:\r\n[http://sigrok.org/wiki/Tondaj_SL-814](http://sigrok.org/wiki/Tondaj_SL-814)\r\n\r\n### Initialize\r\n<pre>serialport.write('\\x10\\x04\\x0d')</pre>\r\n\r\n### Poll\r\n<pre>serialport.write('\\x30\\x00\\x0d')</pre>\r\n\r\nThe sound meter is polled continually, but only records data above the set threshold 70 dB(A) \r\n\r\nIf using the Camera Module, a photo or short video is also captured. \r\n\r\nThe Raspberry Pi hosts a simple web interface to view the data. Install apache or webserver of choice.  (future releases will use node.js for polling and webserver).\r\n\r\n**note: The Pi user will need write permissions for the data, video and img directories in /var/www \r\n\r\nDemo: [http://www.citysoundmap.org/demo.html](http://www.citysoundmap.org/demo.html) (data collected in Moab, UT August 2013). \r\n\r\nPhotos: [http://www.citysoundmap.org](http://www.citysoundmap.org)\r\n\r\n![building the device](http://citysoundmap.org/SoundMap_html_m385bb6d7.jpg)\r\n\r\n![completed case](http://citysoundmap.org/SoundMap_html_m52855a9.jpg)\r\n\r\n![data](http://citysoundmap.org/SoundMap_html_m78939703.png)\r\n\r\n![data and video](http://citysoundmap.org/SoundMap_html_7278ea41.png)","google":"UA-44173693-1","note":"Don't delete this file! It's used internally to help with page regeneration."}